	1.	Comprehensive and Narrative – Written in a clear, detailed narrative (not bullet points), explaining the model and reasoning behind design choices.
	2.	Proportionate to Model Risk – Depth and breadth of documentation should match the model’s risk level, with the highest rigor for high-risk models.
	3.	Consistent and Structured – Follow organizational guidelines (e.g., Risk Tiering, Modular Documentation, Quant Council Writing) to ensure clarity and standardization.